1.00	Kandy_Cricket_Club	Kandy Cricket Club	The Kandy Cricket Club is a first-class cricket club in Sri Lanka which plays at the Asgiriya Stadium, a venue that is also used for Test cricket. Kandy has been a centre of cricket since the 19th century but only attained first-class status in the 1980s after the Sri Lanka national cricket team became a full member of the International Cricket Conference (ICC).	
